                        "etapes": [
                            {
                                "titre": "Felting needles for the uninitiated, are specialty needles designed for felting a bundle of fibers (habitually wool) through repeated insertion and removal (STABBING). These needles have tiny forward-facing barbs that hook the fibers together as the needle is repeatedly inserted into the bundle of fibers, matting them together. If you’ve never taken a stab at needle felting, I implore you to try, it is oddly therapeutic, humbling, and the results are often rewarding.",
