                                "titre": "The Repair Technique In Detail:",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "Here is the simple technique to reverse the effects of nearly all small pulls in upholstery!",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "Preparatory Step: Grasp the felting needle around its shaft, close to the bent end, in your dominant hand between your thumb and index. Use remaining fingers to help support the needle. You are now ready.",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "Step 1: With the felting needle, point down, gingerly stab around the affected area to tighten up the loosened fibers.",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "Step 2: Stab the loop of the pull directly until it becomes recessed back into the fabric.",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "Step 3: Tidy up any stray fibers by stabbing them as well.",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "Step 4: Rub the previously affected area with your fingertips in disbelief.",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
